CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 8, 1957, pg. 1 reads: " Where Boy, 7, Died - James Wilson, 7, of 3487 Milwaukee St. (inset) was struck and killed at Bryn Mawr Dr. and Camp St., Tuesday, by a car driven by George (Kelly) Mosby, 45, of 3157 Ewart Dr. Circles and arrows point where the youngster left the sidewalk and to where he was hit.  Skid marks of the car (traveling left) across the intersection are shown also. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Construction equipment at corner of Bryn Mawr Road and Camp Street with painted arrow and circle marking site of car accident, another version
